{{Infobox software | name = Zabbix | screenshot = Zabbix 3.0.0 dashboard.png | logo = Zabbix logo.png | caption = Zabbix 3.0 dashboard | developer = Zabbix LLC | released = {{start date and age|2001|4}} | latest_release_version = 4.0 LTS<ref name="Release Notes for Zabbix 4.0.0">{{cite web|url=https://www.zabbix.com/rn/rn4.0.0|title=Release Notes for Zabbix}}</ref> | latest_release_date = {{start date and age|2018|10|01}} | latest_preview_version = [https://www.zabbix.com/rn3.4.2rc1 3.4.2rc1] | latest_preview_date = {{start date and age|2017|09|14}} | operating_system = [[Cross-platform]] | programming_language = [[C (programming language)|C]] (server, proxy, agent), [[PHP]] (frontend), [[Java (programming language)|Java]] (Java gateway) | status = active | genre = [[Network management system]] | license = [[GNU General Public License version 2]] | website = {{URL|https://www.zabbix.com}} }}
'''Zabbix''' is an [[open-source software|open-source]] [[network monitoring|monitoring]] software tool for diverse IT components, including [[computer network|networks]], [[Server (computing)|servers]], [[virtual machine]]s (VMs) and [[cloud service]]s. Zabbix provides monitoring metrics, among others network utilization, CPU load and disk space consumption. Zabbix monitoring configuration can be done using XML based templates which contains elements to monitor.<ref>https://www.zabbix.com/documentation/4.0/manual/config/templates</ref> The software monitors operations on Linux, Hewlett Packard Unix (HP-UX), Mac OS X, Solaris and other operating systems (OSes); however, Windows monitoring is only possible through agents. Zabbix can use [[MySQL]], [[MariaDB]], [[PostgreSQL]], [[SQLite]], [[Oracle database|Oracle]] or [[IBM DB2]] to store data.<ref>[https://www.zabbix.com/documentation/3.4/manual/installation/requirements#software List of supported databases in the manual]</ref> Its backend is written in [[C (programming language)|C]] and the web frontend is written in [[PHP]]. Zabbix offers several monitoring options: *Simple checks can verify the availability and responsiveness of standard services such as SMTP or HTTP without installing any software on the monitored host. *A Zabbix [[Software agent|agent]] can also be installed on UNIX and Windows hosts to monitor statistics such as CPU load, network utilization, disk space, etc. *As an alternative to installing an agent on hosts, Zabbix includes support for monitoring via [[Simple Network Management Protocol|SNMP]], [[Transmission Control Protocol|TCP]] and [[Internet Control Message Protocol|ICMP]] checks, as well as over [[Intelligent Platform Management Interface|IPMI]], [[Java Management Extensions|JMX]], [[Secure Shell|SSH]], [[Telnet]] and using custom parameters. Zabbix supports a variety of near-real-time notification mechanisms, including [[Extensible Messaging and Presence Protocol|XMPP]].
Released under the terms of [[GNU General Public License version 2]], Zabbix is [[free software]]. {{TOC limit}}
==History== Zabbix started as an internal software project in 1998. After three years, in 2001, it was released to the public under GPL,<ref name="presentation for netways" /> three years later until the first stable version, 1.0, was released in 2004. [[File:Zabbix Dashboard.png|thumb|Zabbix 2.4 Dashboard page]] [[File:Zabbix 3.0.0 dashboard.png|thumb|Dashboard of the Zabbix 3.0.0 release]] [[File:Zabbix 3.4.0 dashboard dark.png|thumb|Dashboard of the Zabbix 3.4.0 release, dark theme]]
